  Priority order:Inline > Internal > External

4.Color property
    Used to set the color of foreground

    foreground:Foreground wo hota hai jo user directly dekhta aur padhta hai:
      color          /* text ka color */
      opacity        /* content ki transparency */
      z-index        /* kis element ko upar dikhana hai */
      border         /* element ka outline */

5.Background color

6.Color Systems
  ->RGB :color:  rgb(255, 0, 0);
  ->Hex (Hexadecimal) : color : #ff0000;
  
7.Selectors
  ->Universal Selector : *{ }

  ->Class Selector : .myClass { }

  ->Element Selector : 1 { }

  ->Id Selector : #myId { }

8.Text Properties

   ->text-align : left / right / center
   ->text-decoration : underline / overline / line-through
   ->font-weight : normal / bold / bolder / lighter
   ->font-weight : 100-900
   -> line-height :16px(by default)
   ->text-tranform : uppercase / lowercase / capitalize / none
   ->font-family

9.Units in CSS  
 <h5>Absolute</h5>
  pixels (px)--96px = 1 inch

  <h5>Relative</h5>
  %- size as relative to an element's parent object.
  em-font sixe of the parent 
  rem-font size of the root element

  <h5>others</h5>
  vh: relative to 1% viewport height 
  vw : relative to 1% viewport width 


10.Box Model in CSS
   
->Height
->Width
->Border
      <h4>
          border-width : 2px;
          border-style : solid / dotted / dashed
          border-color : black;
      </h4>
      <pre>shorthand form : border:2px solid black;</pre>
  
->border-radius
->padding
          <h4>Shorthand</h4>
          padding: 50px;
          padding: 1px 2px 3px 4px;
                   top | right | bottom | left -> clockwise  

->margin
        <h4>Shorthand</h4>
        margin: 50px;
        
        margin: 1px 2px 3px 4px;
        
               top | right | bottom | left -> clockwise

11.Display Property
    display: inline / block / inline-block / none

12.Visibility
    visibility: hidden; 
    <span>Note : When visibility is set to none, space for the element is reserved.
    But for display set to none, no space is reserved or blocked for the
    element.
    </span>

13.opacity (0 to 1)
       color:  rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.5);
       color:  rgba(255, 0, 0, 1);

****14.Position:how an element is positioned in a document.
   
     position : static / relative / absolute / fixed

     <imp>jis element ko <h5>Position absolute</h5>bante hai woh uppar utta jata aur piche wala element agy a jayega.</imp>

     <imp>jis element ko <h5> Position relative</h5> bante hai uske andhar hume rakna hota hai.</imp>

     <imp>In case of position absolute element containing another element which is position element.In this case first position absolute element will be acting as a postion relative.</imp>

15.z-index :It decides the stack level of elements
  👉 z-index decide karta hai ki kaunsa element upar dikhega aur kaunsa neeche, jab elements overlap kar rahe hote hain.
  <pre>
    Rule:
    z-index value jitni zyada, element utna upar

    1. Basic Concept

    Socho aapne cards ko ek-dusre ke upar rakh diya 📄
    Jo card upar hoga → higher z-index
  </pre>
  <b>Important Rule (MOST IMPORTANT – interview favorite)

❗ z-index tabhi kaam karta hai jab element positioned ho

position: relative | absolute | fixed | sticky


❌ Ye kaam nahi karega:

position: static; /* default */</b>

